Subject: [PATCH] Fix memory leak in network driver subsystem
Date: Tue, 15 Feb 2005 09:30:00 +0000
Message-Id: <nice003.test@kernel.example.org>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

From: Jane Developer <jane@example.org>

This patch fixes a memory leak in the network driver subsystem that
was introduced in commit 3a4b5c6d. The issue occurs when the driver
fails to properly release DMA buffers during error recovery.

The fix ensures that all allocated DMA buffers are freed before
returning from the error path. This was found using valgrind and
confirmed by stress testing with the network driver under heavy load.

Signed-off-by: Jane Developer <jane@example.org>

---
 drivers/net/ethernet/example/driver.c | 12 ++++++------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/example/driver.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/example/driver.c
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/example/driver.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/example/driver.c
@@ -142,6 +142,7 @@ static int driver_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 err_alloc:
+       dma_free_coherent(&pdev->dev, DMA_BUFFER_SIZE, buf, dma_addr);
        pci_release_regions(pdev);
        return -ENOMEM;
